<build>
  <plugins>
    <plugin>
      <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
      <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>
      <version>3.1.2</version>
      <configuration>
        <systemPropertyVariables>
          <env>${env}</env>
          <browser>${browser}</browser>
          <baseUrl>${base.url}</baseUrl>
        </systemPropertyVariables>
      </configuration>
    </plugin>
  </plugins>
</build>


public class TestConfig {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Env: " + System.getProperty("env"));
        System.out.println("Browser: " + System.getProperty("browser"));
        System.out.println("Base URL: " + System.getProperty("baseUrl"));
    }
}

Step 5: You can override them at runtime ðŸ’ª

If you run:

mvn test -Denv=UAT -Dbrowser=edge -Dbase.url=https://uat.example.com

Step 6: (Optional) Set defaults inside <properties> but overrideable

You can keep safe defaults in your POM:

<properties>
  <env>QA</env>
  <browser>chrome</browser>
</properties>